showertime!

I got home on Sunday night, but I have just been a horrible person and haven't updated until now. I have so many stories from my trip. Oh wow! If you'd like to hear some of them just let me know and I'll either e-mail you or call you or something. But there are just too many too put in here. All I can say about my trip is this, it inspired me and confirmed any doubts I had about my life and where I am supposed to go with it. I know for sure that I must be involved with theatre forever. That is my passion and that makes my life whole, without it I will never be fulfilled. So yea, that made me happy. 

Erik is leaving for a week to go to Cali, which I am so envious of cause I way wanna go to Cali...haha, but yea that's kinda sad, but I'll be out of town too. I am going to Leadership Camp for drama 4 days next week so it won't be so bad. I am way excited about it. I need to call people and get costumes set up because I don't have any of that done. Oh well, you can always do that later right?! 

So ummm...oh yea, my brother came home last night! Thanks to all of ya'll who came over to welcome him home. He was thrilled with that. He really was. He is sleeping now, of course. But that cake made some good breakfast! And Brian I did get up to give you your skateboard! HAHA!!! 

Well, this post is getting kinda long so I'm gonna like ummmm go soon. Give me a call if you wanna hang out today, I'm just gonna be bumming around the house listening to stories about Jesse's trip and telling stories from my trip. 

Later!

<3 ~ Chelsea

things are going so great. everything is just like a dream come true. i am in love with the most perfect guy in the world. he makes me so happy and fills me with an even greater passion for life and for my dreams of theatre and everything. i have never been happier with myself, my friends, my family, and any guy. life is truly amazing and every moment that i spend with erik he shows me that and he also shows me that some things dont have to be so difficult. some things are just meant to be and you dont have to work so hard at them. so thank you, erik. i love you more than you know.

ok well i think that is about it....i am gonna go have a smoke with my mom and scott whenever he gets here. if anyone wants to hang out tonight just give me a call...love you guys!

MWAH!

so yea footloose is on in like 20 minutes and thats all i have to look forward to. 

i went to the doctor today and guess what she told me?

she said, "chelsea you have strep throat! take these pills and you should feel better in 24-48 hours!" she told me that my throat was so swollen that she didnt even need to run a test to see if it was strep throat or not, cause it definately was. so now i have meds for it and maybe ill feel better. the first real food i ate in 3 days was 1/2 of a cheeseburger a little while ago. at least it was something. ive lost 5 lbs in the past 3 days cause i havent been able to eat. but yea...its all good. 

mom has a major migraine and she is freaking out about money. our mortgage went up like $200 and she just took like $140 pay cut for her new job. so i dont know what we are gonna do. if any of yall know of a job that starts at around $13 an hr, please let me know cause she is seriously getting so worked up about every little thing and just like freaks out when she hears about people making money and i dont know its crazy. i want to help her. 

anycow...im off to take more meds and get better hopefully. if ive "swapped spit" with any of yall im sorry cause you might have the strep throat thing too! and that would suck. haha. but yea i gotta get going and go watch some footloose, since thats all i can do. 

if youre bored and wanna stop by, feel free to. haha. bye.

mwah!

are you fighting for?
give up
give in 
pull the plug
pull the trigger
its all over 
its all done
you make no difference
to anyone
why are you here
why arent you there
why do you run away like that
cowering behind the trees
it isnt as if you are hidden
did you know that
we can all still see you 
there is something different about you though
something in your eyes
its something about the way they are always beaming these rays of light
even in the night
when it is dark and cold and rainy and wet
but you still run 
you still hide
you will never forget...
i hope someone saves you 
before you fall 
before you fall too far
before you fall too far down and you are 
trapped
trapped
buried alive
suffocating to death 
under walls of dirt, deceit, lies
what are you fighting for?
are you fighting for your life?
or theirs?
what difference does it make?
